WEBVTT

00:02.567 --> 00:04.307
- [breathing heavily]

00:04.352 --> 00:05.922
[dogs barking]

00:05.962 --> 00:08.922
[eerie music]

00:08.965 --> 00:10.835
♪

00:10.880 --> 00:12.530
[screams]

00:12.577 --> 00:15.097
Mommy!
Mommy!

00:16.494 --> 00:18.324
Mom!
Mom!

00:18.366 --> 00:20.146
- Cindy?
Cindy, honey?

00:20.194 --> 00:22.154
Cindy?

00:22.196 --> 00:24.716
[dramatic music]

00:24.763 --> 00:26.113
What is it?

00:26.156 --> 00:28.846
- I saw Daddy.
He wants to change me.

00:28.898 --> 00:31.208
I don't want to be like him!

00:31.248 --> 00:34.988
- Baby, it's okay now.

00:35.035 --> 00:38.255
Daddy is far, far away.

00:38.299 --> 00:41.609
And he won't find us.
All right?

00:41.650 --> 00:48.610
♪

01:19.905 --> 01:22.865
[low eerie music]

01:22.908 --> 01:29.958
♪

01:37.706 --> 01:40.666
[music intensifies]

01:40.709 --> 01:42.359
♪

01:42.406 --> 01:45.016
- [snarling]

01:45.061 --> 01:49.241
♪

01:49.283 --> 01:52.333
- [screams]

02:03.471 --> 02:04.911
[clears throat]

02:07.910 --> 02:10.960
[indistinct chatter]

02:17.833 --> 02:22.323
- Leave my grandson out of
whatever mischief you're up to.

02:22.359 --> 02:26.059
[dramatic music]

02:26.102 --> 02:28.102
- I can talk to whoever I want.

02:28.148 --> 02:32.018
- You'll stay away from him.

02:32.064 --> 02:35.984
Your father was a monster,
and so are you.

02:39.071 --> 02:40.901
- And Jordan Mahkent
was a loser

02:40.943 --> 02:44.733
who got turned into ice cubes
by a pickup truck.

02:44.773 --> 02:48.393
[eerie whooshing]

02:52.346 --> 02:53.906
Hmm.

02:59.048 --> 03:01.398
[ice crackling]

03:03.270 --> 03:06.190
[heroic music]

03:06.229 --> 03:13.239
♪

03:21.244 --> 03:24.254
[Staff humming and beeping]

03:25.901 --> 03:27.381
- [sighs]

03:29.557 --> 03:31.907
- It's an hour past curfew.
- [yelps]

03:31.950 --> 03:34.910
Hey.

03:34.953 --> 03:38.393
Yeah, well...

03:38.435 --> 03:40.565
what are you doing in my room?

03:40.611 --> 03:42.091
- I was waiting
to show you something.

03:42.134 --> 03:43.664
Where were you?

03:43.701 --> 03:45.571
- I was out.

03:47.444 --> 03:50.584
[sighs]
Looking for The Shade.

03:51.753 --> 03:55.283
- The Shade?
Why?

03:55.322 --> 03:57.762
- I ran into him
at the bookstore today.

03:57.802 --> 04:00.332
He was the one who told me
about Dr. Mid-Nite's daughter

04:00.370 --> 04:02.940
and how Eclipso killed her.

04:05.201 --> 04:09.211
A super-villain was more honest
with me than my own stepfather.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.899
- Okay, Court--
- So I went out to go find him,

04:11.947 --> 04:14.337
to learn more,
to ask him to team up.

04:14.384 --> 04:16.474
- To team up?

04:16.517 --> 04:18.207
Have you not
been paying attention?

04:18.258 --> 04:19.998
The Shade is a bad guy.

04:20.042 --> 04:22.612
- Eclipso is evil.

04:22.653 --> 04:25.403
There's a difference.

04:25.439 --> 04:28.139
- We don't need The Shade
to find the black diamond.

04:28.180 --> 04:30.310
We've got the weather.

04:30.357 --> 04:32.657
- The weather?

04:32.707 --> 04:35.007
- The black diamond
brings out a darkness,

04:35.057 --> 04:38.577
not just in people
but in places.

04:38.626 --> 04:40.236
The weather in Nebraska
this week,

04:40.280 --> 04:42.930
clear and sunny statewide.

04:42.978 --> 04:45.498
Except for Blue Valley.

04:45.546 --> 04:47.636
I think it's because
Eclipso is here.

04:47.678 --> 04:49.198
- Even if that's true,

04:49.245 --> 04:52.195
how does bad weather
help us find the diamond?

04:54.119 --> 04:56.339
- I'm not sure.

04:56.383 --> 04:59.213
Yeah, I don't know, but we're
gonna play this out,

04:59.255 --> 05:00.995
and we're not gonna ask
The Shade for help.

05:01.039 --> 05:03.349
He's killed people, Court.

05:06.784 --> 05:08.794
He's not on our side.

05:11.876 --> 05:13.396
- Pat.

05:15.445 --> 05:17.795
I'll stick to the curfew.

05:17.839 --> 05:19.279
I'm sorry.

05:21.103 --> 05:24.283
- I'm sorry I didn't tell you
about Dr. Mid-Nite's daughter.

05:26.108 --> 05:28.198
- And you're sure

05:28.240 --> 05:30.070
there's nothing else?

05:30.112 --> 05:31.462
Because...

05:33.855 --> 05:36.155
- Yeah.
Get some rest.

05:36.205 --> 05:39.155
[dramatic music]

05:39.208 --> 05:45.738
♪

05:45.780 --> 05:47.520
[sighs]

05:47.564 --> 05:51.444
[dog panting]

05:51.481 --> 05:52.831
[dog whimpers]

05:52.874 --> 05:55.754
Hey.
Don't give me that look.

05:57.357 --> 06:00.747
[thunder booming]
[dog whines]

06:02.231 --> 06:04.541
Okay.
You can sleep with us tonight.

06:04.581 --> 06:05.891
Come on.
Let's go.

06:05.930 --> 06:08.980
[thunder booming]

06:15.462 --> 06:18.472
[rain pattering]

06:25.950 --> 06:28.910
[indistinct shouting]

06:34.176 --> 06:38.436
[wind whistling]

06:38.485 --> 06:39.695
- Hey, Dad.

06:44.708 --> 06:47.358
[wind gusting]

06:47.407 --> 06:50.367
[eerie music]

06:50.410 --> 06:57.070
♪

07:04.815 --> 07:06.505
[sighs]

07:08.906 --> 07:12.816
[thunder booming]

07:12.867 --> 07:19.737
♪

07:20.701 --> 07:23.011
[thunder booming]

07:25.096 --> 07:28.056
[light music]

07:28.099 --> 07:31.669
♪

07:31.712 --> 07:32.932
- Cam!

07:35.150 --> 07:38.110
- Hey.
- How's the mural, my man?

07:38.153 --> 07:39.893
- Good,
but it might rain,

07:39.937 --> 07:42.677
so I came in to use the studio,
if that's all right.

07:42.723 --> 07:43.723
- Have at it.

07:43.767 --> 07:44.807
- Cool.
Thanks.

07:44.855 --> 07:47.205
Oh.

07:47.249 --> 07:49.339
Um...

07:49.381 --> 07:53.651
♪

07:53.690 --> 07:55.950
- That looks a lot
like Courtney Whitmore to me.

07:55.997 --> 08:00.477
- [laughs] I was--
I was just fooling around.

08:00.523 --> 08:04.533
- Or maybe...
you found your muse.

08:04.571 --> 08:06.881
♪

08:06.921 --> 08:10.321
Every great artist has one.

08:10.359 --> 08:13.059
Back when I was doing the best
work of my life, I did.

08:13.101 --> 08:19.671
♪

08:19.716 --> 08:23.976
Anyway, now I'm inspired
to help others find theirs.

08:24.025 --> 08:26.415
- Hi.
[laughs]

08:27.855 --> 08:29.935
- Hi.

08:29.987 --> 08:32.247
Good morning.

08:32.294 --> 08:33.604
- Class is about to start.

08:33.643 --> 08:35.383
We have a lot to talk about.

08:35.427 --> 08:37.557
Like the weather.

08:37.604 --> 08:38.564
- Right.

08:38.605 --> 08:40.255
The weather.
[laughs]

08:40.302 --> 08:43.262
Daily topic, though,
nothing special about it.

08:43.305 --> 08:45.125
[chuckles]

08:45.176 --> 08:46.996
- Let's go.

08:48.049 --> 08:50.179
- Bye.

08:50.225 --> 08:57.275
♪

08:58.233 --> 09:02.853
- Your art can say
everything you can't.

09:02.890 --> 09:04.810
Show her.

09:04.848 --> 09:11.898
♪

09:15.467 --> 09:17.557
[drip echoes]

09:17.600 --> 09:21.040
[eerie music]

09:21.082 --> 09:22.612
[drip echoes]

09:22.649 --> 09:24.429
♪

09:24.476 --> 09:26.086
[water drips]

09:27.523 --> 09:30.053
[eerie whooshing]

09:30.091 --> 09:37.141
♪

09:40.667 --> 09:42.097
- Hi.

09:43.800 --> 09:45.980
- Cindy.

09:46.020 --> 09:48.590
I thought you moved.

09:48.631 --> 09:50.851
What are you doing here?

09:50.894 --> 09:54.034
- You know, I'd really love
to see some of your work.

09:54.071 --> 09:57.901
I'm sure it's...
better than this.

09:57.945 --> 09:59.285
[laughs]

10:03.690 --> 10:05.910
Sorry about your dad.

10:05.953 --> 10:09.003
[thunder rumbling]

10:10.653 --> 10:12.353
- You remember what you said
to our fourth grade class

10:12.394 --> 10:14.314
after your mom died?

10:14.352 --> 10:15.792
[dramatic music]

10:15.832 --> 10:20.582
You said,
"I never liked her anyway,"

10:20.620 --> 10:22.840
right in front of everyone.

10:24.536 --> 10:26.356
No one ever forgot that, Cindy.

10:28.018 --> 10:30.588
So do not tell me

10:30.630 --> 10:32.590
you're sorry about my dad.

10:33.807 --> 10:35.637
You've never been sorry.

10:38.376 --> 10:40.676
About anything.

10:40.727 --> 10:47.727
♪

10:52.739 --> 10:54.259
- Cam!

10:58.440 --> 11:00.360
Your sketchbook.

11:00.398 --> 11:02.488
It was right in my hand.

11:02.531 --> 11:04.101
- Thanks, Paul.

11:04.141 --> 11:06.841
I think I'll go
take my chances with the rain.

11:06.883 --> 11:08.713
- Good luck, my man.

11:10.582 --> 11:12.372
Miss Burman!

11:12.410 --> 11:14.110
You're back

11:14.151 --> 11:16.981
and showing an interest in art,
I see.

11:17.024 --> 11:18.984
- Hmm.

11:19.026 --> 11:22.506
[eerie whispering]

11:22.551 --> 11:24.731
I dropped out, Paul.

11:24.771 --> 11:29.121
♪

11:29.166 --> 11:32.126
[ethereal music]

11:32.169 --> 11:35.299
♪

11:35.346 --> 11:37.346
- Hello.

11:37.392 --> 11:39.392
- What?

11:39.437 --> 11:41.787
Who said that?

11:41.831 --> 11:45.401
- I'm your new muse.

11:48.229 --> 11:50.059
- Is someone there?

11:55.845 --> 11:58.805
[tense music]

11:58.848 --> 12:01.548
♪

12:04.941 --> 12:08.471
[bell tolling]

12:08.510 --> 12:11.770
[thunder rumbling]

12:11.818 --> 12:13.378
- Ah, Ms. Whitmore.
- [gasps]

12:13.428 --> 12:16.468
- Whoops-a-daisy.
I trust the day finds you well?

12:16.518 --> 12:17.998
- [sighs]

12:18.041 --> 12:20.611
[dramatic music]

12:20.652 --> 12:22.872
- I know who you really are,
Shade.

12:22.916 --> 12:24.866
What are you doing here?

12:24.918 --> 12:27.878
- Look at you, all fired up.

12:27.921 --> 12:30.971
I see where your daughter
gets her bravado,

12:31.011 --> 12:34.061
and you have an extra quality.

12:34.101 --> 12:36.631
It reminds me of someone.

12:38.714 --> 12:40.064
[chuckles]

12:40.107 --> 12:41.937
Someone from long ago.

12:41.978 --> 12:45.068
- Don't get any ideas.

12:45.112 --> 12:47.242
I had enough
of your buddy Jordan

12:47.288 --> 12:49.588
seeing me
as some sort of sick prize.

12:49.638 --> 12:53.688
- Aw, Ms. Whitmore,
you mistake my intentions.

12:53.729 --> 12:56.819
The person you remind me of...

12:56.863 --> 12:58.783
was family.

12:59.517 --> 13:02.827
Now, as to why I'm here?

13:02.869 --> 13:06.959
Your daughter spent last night
searching for me.

13:07.003 --> 13:09.093
You simply must tell her

13:09.136 --> 13:12.566
to refrain
from interfering in my affairs.

13:12.617 --> 13:14.967
- We want to know what you know

13:15.011 --> 13:16.881
about the black diamond,

13:16.926 --> 13:19.406
this weird weather.

13:19.450 --> 13:23.670
- Oh, so you worked
that much out.

13:23.715 --> 13:25.365
But, Ms. Whitmore,

13:25.413 --> 13:27.893
the weather is simply
the prelude.

13:27.937 --> 13:30.717
Believe me,

13:30.766 --> 13:33.456
you do not want
to see the finale.

13:34.814 --> 13:37.214
Now...

13:37.251 --> 13:42.871
better that you never speak
of that cursed gem again.

13:42.909 --> 13:46.219
And as for your daughter
and her friends...

13:47.914 --> 13:50.704
They're far too young
to face the horror within.

13:50.742 --> 13:54.092
I warn you.

13:56.574 --> 13:58.364
- You came here to warn me?

13:58.402 --> 14:00.802
Why do you even care?

14:00.840 --> 14:03.360
- Oh, trust me, I do not.

14:03.407 --> 14:05.057
But if your daughter,

14:05.105 --> 14:07.625
in all her tiresome snooping,

14:07.672 --> 14:10.152
gets wind of the location
of the black diamond,

14:10.197 --> 14:13.287
she'd be well advised
to give that information to you

14:13.330 --> 14:14.940
to convey to me.

14:16.377 --> 14:20.117
It's by far the safest course
of action for your family.

14:22.035 --> 14:24.515
And you and Pat Dugan know it.

14:27.214 --> 14:29.874
- Even if I did believe you,

14:29.912 --> 14:31.352
that card you gave me

14:31.392 --> 14:33.442
had no way to contact you.

14:34.264 --> 14:36.094
- Perhaps you should
take another look.

14:36.136 --> 14:42.526
♪

14:42.577 --> 14:45.617
[sizzling]

14:55.416 --> 14:57.106
- [sighs]

14:57.157 --> 14:59.587
[eerie whooshing]

14:59.637 --> 15:06.427
♪

15:07.471 --> 15:09.781
- Welcome back to
"The Lady Bob and Steve Show"

15:09.821 --> 15:12.131
here on WWPX radio.

15:12.172 --> 15:13.872
- And how about
this wacky weather

15:13.913 --> 15:15.443
here in Blue Valley, huh?

15:15.479 --> 15:17.049
Meteorologists
calling for sunshine,

15:17.090 --> 15:18.740
but all I see are clouds
and thunderstorms

15:18.787 --> 15:20.957
on the horizon.
- Hey, but on the good side,

15:21.007 --> 15:23.787
bear break-ins are down 100%

15:23.835 --> 15:25.925
compared to just over
one week ago,

15:25.968 --> 15:28.448
when Yogi seemed to be
making himself--

15:28.492 --> 15:29.932
[dramatic music]

15:29.972 --> 15:31.672
- Where are we going, Mom?

15:31.713 --> 15:33.413
- Your dad and I are going away
for a little while.

15:34.977 --> 15:37.497
- Mom, Dad, don't leave me!

15:37.545 --> 15:42.325
♪

15:42.376 --> 15:44.726
- [roaring]

15:45.466 --> 15:47.466
- 30 minutes of nonstop hits

15:47.511 --> 15:50.651
starting right now
on the PX.

15:50.688 --> 15:53.648
[Black River Delta's
"Burning and Burning"]

15:53.691 --> 15:59.351
♪

16:01.743 --> 16:05.663
- ♪ I've been
a soulless child ♪

16:05.703 --> 16:08.013
♪ I've been a soulless child

16:08.054 --> 16:09.454
[engine revving]

16:09.490 --> 16:11.490
♪ I was a messed-up kid

16:11.535 --> 16:13.925
♪ With a thorn in my side

16:13.973 --> 16:17.283
♪

16:17.324 --> 16:20.464
♪ They said
I bet you die young, son ♪

16:20.501 --> 16:23.771
♪ Yeah, I bet you die young

16:23.808 --> 16:25.768
- Do you need something?

16:27.421 --> 16:29.551
- From you?

16:29.597 --> 16:32.027
Nope.

16:32.078 --> 16:34.118
- ♪ So are you

16:34.167 --> 16:39.427
♪ Trying to change my ways

16:39.476 --> 16:42.386
♪ Oh, you see,
I'm burning and burning ♪

16:42.436 --> 16:46.566
♪ All the way down
[tires squealing]

16:46.614 --> 16:48.014
- Jerk.

16:50.096 --> 16:52.616
[thunder rumbling]

16:52.663 --> 16:54.883
- The weather is the key.

16:54.926 --> 16:57.626
If we use the goggles to track
the patterns, then we--

16:57.668 --> 17:00.758
- You said you saw
Dr. Mid-Nite die, Mr. Dugan.

17:00.802 --> 17:02.542
- I did, but it can't be
that that's what--

17:02.586 --> 17:04.366
- It could be!
- All right, well, Beth,

17:04.414 --> 17:06.294
I'm just trying to tell you--
- No, it could be.

17:06.329 --> 17:08.549
- Guys, hey.
What's going on?

17:08.592 --> 17:10.122
- Rick!

17:10.159 --> 17:12.549
I heard him through
the goggles last night.

17:12.596 --> 17:13.896
- Chuck?

17:13.945 --> 17:17.035
- Not Chuck,
Dr. Charles McNider,

17:17.079 --> 17:18.859
the first Dr. Mid-Nite!

17:18.907 --> 17:21.737
[laughs]
That's why he didn't know me.

17:21.779 --> 17:24.739
- So the goggles
are a Ouija board now?

17:24.782 --> 17:26.962
- They can't talk
to the dead, Beth.

17:27.002 --> 17:29.142
- So maybe
he's still alive somewhere,

17:29.178 --> 17:33.098
and wherever he is,
he might need our help.

17:33.139 --> 17:36.099
- Listen, I hope
that it is Dr. McNider,

17:36.142 --> 17:37.712
more than anything,

17:37.752 --> 17:40.362
but that's exactly
why we need to be cautious.

17:40.407 --> 17:42.057
Could be Eclipso, Beth.

17:42.104 --> 17:44.154
[ominous music]

17:44.193 --> 17:46.203
He can make you see things,

17:46.239 --> 17:48.239
hear things,

17:48.284 --> 17:50.984
things you fear,
things you want.

17:51.026 --> 17:55.596
♪

17:55.639 --> 17:59.249
- But what if Beth
is right, Pat?

17:59.295 --> 18:02.255
[somber music]

18:02.298 --> 18:04.818
♪

18:04.866 --> 18:07.386
- [sighs] I mean,
that was your teammate.

18:07.434 --> 18:11.224
♪

18:11.264 --> 18:13.144
- If Beth's right

18:13.179 --> 18:15.749
and Dr. McNider is alive,

18:15.790 --> 18:18.710
then we won't rest
until we find him.

18:20.403 --> 18:22.883
But until you hear
his voice again,

18:22.927 --> 18:25.367
we need to focus
on the weather patterns.

18:26.714 --> 18:28.724
And finding the black diamond.

18:28.759 --> 18:32.809
♪

18:32.850 --> 18:35.510
[thunder rumbling]

18:36.202 --> 18:41.122
- [coughing]

18:41.163 --> 18:42.733
[clears throat]

18:42.773 --> 18:44.653
Excuse me.

18:44.688 --> 18:48.168
And okay, the last
of the famous conflicts

18:48.214 --> 18:49.784
to consider for your report

18:49.824 --> 18:53.094
is one of my faves,
the Trojan War,

18:53.132 --> 18:56.532
reportedly fought in honor
of a woman, Helen of Troy.

18:56.570 --> 18:59.050
[chuckles]

18:59.094 --> 19:01.754
A historical muse, if you will.

19:01.792 --> 19:06.932
♪

19:06.971 --> 19:10.411
[coughs, clears throat]

19:10.453 --> 19:13.243
Excuse me again, I...

19:13.282 --> 19:15.112
Where was I?

19:15.154 --> 19:18.164
[coughing]

19:21.072 --> 19:23.602
Why don't we end
a few minutes early today?

19:23.640 --> 19:25.290
I'll see you all tomorrow.

19:25.338 --> 19:29.388
[eerie whispering]

19:29.429 --> 19:35.219
♪

19:35.261 --> 19:37.921
[retching]

19:37.959 --> 19:40.739
[electricity crackling]

19:40.788 --> 19:47.838
♪

19:59.241 --> 20:02.201
[soft dramatic music]

20:02.244 --> 20:03.814
♪

20:03.854 --> 20:05.814
- You didn't have to come.

20:05.856 --> 20:08.726
- Well, I'm concerned too.

20:08.772 --> 20:11.652
Look at all these.

20:11.688 --> 20:15.648
Remember what
The Thunderbolt said?

20:15.692 --> 20:18.912
Mike's...lonely.

20:18.956 --> 20:20.776
- No, I know,

20:20.828 --> 20:23.218
and I appreciate
your reminding me.

20:23.265 --> 20:25.215
I'll keep that in mind.

20:25.267 --> 20:27.227
- Got plenty of them.
Got a pile out back.

20:27.269 --> 20:28.659
I'll find you a good one.

20:28.705 --> 20:30.095
- Hey, guys.

20:30.141 --> 20:31.971
- Oh, hey there, Dugan.
- How you doing?

20:32.013 --> 20:35.933
- Well, here she is.
Fun for the whole family.

20:35.973 --> 20:38.593
$50 discount
if you take her away right now.

20:38.628 --> 20:40.538
- Yeah, well, we're not gonna

20:40.587 --> 20:42.277
be getting a station wagon,
Zeek,

20:42.328 --> 20:44.288
but I do appreciate
your calling me,

20:44.330 --> 20:45.810
and it's good to see you.

20:45.853 --> 20:47.903
- Yeah, you too.

20:50.466 --> 20:52.026
- So what are you doing?

20:53.556 --> 20:57.036
- Trying to help.
- By buying a car?

20:57.081 --> 20:59.741
- Well, yeah.

20:59.780 --> 21:01.260
I figured once it's souped up,

21:01.303 --> 21:03.783
it would be a good getaway car

21:03.827 --> 21:05.567
for the team.

21:05.612 --> 21:07.052
- Okay, Dugan.

21:07.091 --> 21:08.531
[laughing] Okay.

21:08.571 --> 21:12.011
$75 off, final offer.
Take her away!

21:12.053 --> 21:13.973
- Say, Zeek, you mind

21:14.011 --> 21:16.881
just giving us a minute
so we can talk?

21:16.927 --> 21:18.147
- Oh, yeah, sure thing.

21:18.189 --> 21:19.369
You all take all the time
you need.

21:19.408 --> 21:20.928
And don't forget:
you break it--

21:20.975 --> 21:22.455
- You buy it, got it.

21:22.498 --> 21:23.888
- Hey.
- I remember.

21:23.934 --> 21:25.114
- I like that,
got a nice ring to it.

21:25.153 --> 21:26.633
Miss.

21:26.676 --> 21:29.546
- So, Mike, you can't be
dragging me and Barb

21:29.592 --> 21:31.122
all the way out here, okay?

21:31.159 --> 21:32.989
- I don't mind the trip.

21:33.770 --> 21:36.560
- I appreciate the initiative,
Mike, the drive.

21:36.599 --> 21:39.079
I mean, I wish you had it
in school and at your job,

21:39.123 --> 21:41.473
but it's a goal
we can work towards,

21:41.517 --> 21:45.607
but what's going on now,
it's dangerous.

21:46.696 --> 21:49.046
- I know.
The Shade, I was--

21:49.090 --> 21:50.790
- And more.

21:50.831 --> 21:54.491
I get your frustration, Mike,
more than you know, okay?

21:54.530 --> 21:56.360
I understand it.

21:56.402 --> 21:59.192
[warm music]

21:59.230 --> 22:06.020
♪

22:06.063 --> 22:09.073
So let's find a JSA project

22:09.110 --> 22:12.240
that we can work on.

22:12.287 --> 22:14.157
Together.
- Really?

22:14.202 --> 22:15.772
- Yeah, you know,

22:15.812 --> 22:18.122
we'll start
with a small one and--

22:18.162 --> 22:19.472
- Yeah, yeah, it's--
- Okay?

22:19.512 --> 22:22.382
- It's cool.
It's great.

22:22.428 --> 22:24.258
- It'll be good. Yeah.

22:24.299 --> 22:26.739
- Awesome.
- Yeah.

22:26.780 --> 22:29.440
♪

22:29.478 --> 22:31.958
- Thanks, Dad.

22:32.002 --> 22:33.402
- You got it.

22:33.439 --> 22:35.139
[pats back]

22:35.179 --> 22:37.359
All right.
Let's head home.

22:39.401 --> 22:42.971
[thunder booming]

22:43.013 --> 22:46.673
- Abuela's knees always ache
when it rains.

22:46.713 --> 22:48.373
- How are your headaches?

22:49.672 --> 22:51.852
- Better, actually.

22:51.892 --> 22:55.072
I've been so focused
on Eclipso.

22:55.112 --> 22:57.592
Maybe it's taken my mind off
what happened a bit.

22:57.637 --> 22:59.547
[indistinct shouting]

22:59.595 --> 23:01.375
- You go on ahead.

23:02.859 --> 23:05.469
Look, Pat and my mom

23:05.514 --> 23:07.214
said no matter
what we're dealing with,

23:07.255 --> 23:09.475
we can't let the rest
of our lives fall apart.

23:11.390 --> 23:14.480
I'll--I'll catch up.
- Courtney.

23:14.523 --> 23:16.743
- If anything big happens,
text me.

23:16.786 --> 23:23.836
♪

23:26.927 --> 23:30.667
Whoa.
It's really coming along.

23:30.713 --> 23:32.243
- Thanks.

23:32.280 --> 23:34.370
- I love the colors.

23:35.979 --> 23:38.069
Is that...

23:38.112 --> 23:41.862
- Yeah, it's gonna be
my dad.

23:41.898 --> 23:44.948
[wind gusting]

23:52.648 --> 23:56.218
You know, I wanted
to show you something,

23:56.260 --> 23:59.530
but it's--it's kind of weird.

24:00.743 --> 24:02.483
- Weird how?

24:03.964 --> 24:08.274
- Well, usually
I do still lifes,

24:08.316 --> 24:12.056
but lately, I've started
trying my hand

24:12.102 --> 24:14.632
at people.

24:14.670 --> 24:21.720
♪

24:25.246 --> 24:27.546
- It's me.
[laughs]

24:27.596 --> 24:28.946
- Yeah.

24:28.989 --> 24:36.039
♪

24:42.481 --> 24:45.441
[ethereal music]

24:45.484 --> 24:49.444
♪

24:49.488 --> 24:51.578
- [coughs]

24:51.620 --> 24:53.930
- You have been blessed.

24:53.970 --> 24:57.280
[eerie whispering]

24:57.321 --> 24:58.711
- Who are you?

24:58.758 --> 25:01.458
- I am your inspiration,
your muse.

25:01.500 --> 25:06.240
Your artistry deserves to be
witnessed again, doesn't it?

25:06.287 --> 25:09.507
- Yes.
- What do you see?

25:09.551 --> 25:16.341
♪

25:16.384 --> 25:17.694
- Nothing.

25:17.733 --> 25:23.483
- What...do...you...see?

25:24.740 --> 25:26.480
- I see.

25:28.614 --> 25:30.574
I see it now.

25:31.965 --> 25:35.925
It's beautiful.

25:35.969 --> 25:40.189
- Show the world.

25:40.234 --> 25:42.154
[cackles]

25:42.192 --> 25:45.152
[tense music]

25:45.195 --> 25:48.975
♪

25:49.025 --> 25:51.325
- Wow.

25:51.375 --> 25:53.765
- My mom loved the yard.

25:53.813 --> 25:55.293
[chuckles]

25:55.336 --> 25:57.556
That's why
they bought the house.

25:57.599 --> 25:59.079
For the gardens.

26:02.604 --> 26:05.224
My grandparents want to move,
but...

26:05.259 --> 26:07.699
Blue Valley is my home.

26:07.740 --> 26:09.660
At least until I graduate.

26:09.698 --> 26:13.088
- Then what?
- Well, I don't know.

26:13.136 --> 26:16.226
I thought maybe I'd go
to art school like my mom,

26:16.270 --> 26:17.620
but now so many people
have told me

26:17.663 --> 26:20.063
how much my dad
has changed their lives,

26:20.100 --> 26:22.450
being an artist
feels kind of selfish.

26:23.277 --> 26:25.667
- [sighs]

26:25.714 --> 26:28.724
Denying the world of your
talent could seem selfish too.

26:28.761 --> 26:30.631
[chuckles]

26:30.676 --> 26:33.636
[warm music]

26:33.679 --> 26:39.379
♪

26:39.423 --> 26:40.993
[cell phone dings and buzzes]

26:41.034 --> 26:42.694
Oops.
Sorry, just--

26:42.731 --> 26:44.171
[laughs]
Um...

26:44.211 --> 26:45.471
- Everything okay?

26:47.606 --> 26:49.906
- Yeah, I--
[cell phone dings and buzzes]

26:49.956 --> 26:52.216
- Um...

26:53.437 --> 26:55.267
I have to go.

26:55.309 --> 26:57.009
I'm so sorry.

26:57.050 --> 26:58.660
- The drawing weirded you out,
didn't it?

26:58.704 --> 27:00.274
- No!
Not at all.

27:00.314 --> 27:03.104
You can sketch me
as many times as you want.

27:03.143 --> 27:04.623
[laughs]
[cell phone dings and buzzes]

27:06.276 --> 27:10.236
I--I really have to go.

27:10.280 --> 27:13.460
[cell phone dinging
and buzzing]

27:13.501 --> 27:16.201
- You did this to me
last year, Courtney.

27:16.243 --> 27:17.683
You always leave.

27:17.723 --> 27:20.163
[somber music]

27:20.203 --> 27:21.813
Or never show.

27:24.120 --> 27:25.600
- Last time.

27:25.644 --> 27:27.864
I promise.

27:27.907 --> 27:29.907
I'm really sorry.

27:29.952 --> 27:33.612
♪

27:33.652 --> 27:35.442
[cell phone dings and buzzes]

27:35.479 --> 27:41.959
♪

27:42.008 --> 27:44.968
[dramatic music]

27:45.011 --> 27:49.931
♪

27:53.236 --> 27:54.756
- I've been tracking
the weather patterns

27:54.803 --> 27:57.283
and the wind's epicenter.
[thunder booming]

27:57.327 --> 27:58.757
[dramatic music]

27:58.807 --> 28:02.157
Yup.
It's right above us.

28:02.202 --> 28:04.032
- Does that mean
the diamond's inside?

28:04.073 --> 28:06.513
- According to Pat,
it's a possibility.

28:06.554 --> 28:08.644
- Where is Pat?
- With Mike.

28:08.687 --> 28:10.947
He's meeting us here.

28:10.993 --> 28:13.003
Said to wait, but--

28:13.039 --> 28:14.389
- What?

28:14.431 --> 28:16.651
- That's Mr. Deisinger's car.

28:16.695 --> 28:19.565
- What's Mr. Deisinger's car
doing here so late?

28:19.610 --> 28:21.660
- If the diamond is in there,

28:21.700 --> 28:23.440
he could be in trouble.

28:23.484 --> 28:26.234
♪

28:26.269 --> 28:29.229
[thunder booming]

28:29.272 --> 28:32.232
[ominous music]

28:32.275 --> 28:39.325
♪

28:40.414 --> 28:43.074
[low growl]

28:43.112 --> 28:44.462
- What is it?

28:46.463 --> 28:48.603
[computer blipping]

28:48.639 --> 28:50.899
- Some kind of
electrical disturbance.

28:50.946 --> 28:53.906
[electricity crackling]

28:53.949 --> 29:00.999
♪

29:31.813 --> 29:33.683
- What the hell happened
in here?

29:35.774 --> 29:37.304
- Where's Mr. Deisinger?

29:37.340 --> 29:44.390
♪

29:48.351 --> 29:51.351
[dark choral music]

29:51.398 --> 29:58.448
♪

30:04.498 --> 30:07.538
[high-pitched ringing]

30:14.203 --> 30:15.733
- Yolanda.

30:15.770 --> 30:18.560
- [screaming]

30:18.599 --> 30:19.819
- Yolanda?

30:19.861 --> 30:22.211
- [grunting]

30:22.255 --> 30:23.685
- Yolanda?

30:23.734 --> 30:25.434
Yolanda!

30:25.475 --> 30:27.125
Yolanda, stop!

30:29.392 --> 30:32.702
[wind gusting]

30:32.743 --> 30:39.793
♪

30:42.362 --> 30:45.632
- [speaking indistinctly,
distortedly]

30:45.669 --> 30:50.499
♪

30:54.069 --> 30:56.719
[dramatic music]

30:56.767 --> 30:58.937
♪

30:58.987 --> 31:00.897
- Court?

31:00.946 --> 31:02.726
- What is that?

31:05.602 --> 31:07.432
- Eclipso.

31:07.474 --> 31:14.524
♪

31:21.444 --> 31:23.144
- Beth, move!

31:25.100 --> 31:26.620
[grunts]

31:26.667 --> 31:33.717
♪

31:36.155 --> 31:38.025
- He's dead because of you.

31:38.940 --> 31:40.640
They both are.

31:42.726 --> 31:45.026
Over here, Rick.

31:46.078 --> 31:48.598
- [roaring]

31:48.645 --> 31:50.865
- Mm, who's the monster?

31:50.909 --> 31:52.169
Him?

31:52.214 --> 31:55.614
- [shouts]
- Or you?

31:57.176 --> 31:59.046
- Shut up.

31:59.091 --> 32:02.011
Shut up!

32:03.269 --> 32:07.009
- Look at what's happening
to your life.

32:07.055 --> 32:10.445
It's being ripped apart.

32:10.493 --> 32:12.583
- You don't have time
for this family anymore.

32:12.626 --> 32:14.666
- You never wanted
this family!

32:16.325 --> 32:18.235
- [screams]

32:18.284 --> 32:20.114
- Guys!

32:20.155 --> 32:23.325
- [grunting]

32:23.376 --> 32:25.196
- I can fix this.

32:25.247 --> 32:27.597
- [shouting]

32:27.641 --> 32:33.691
♪

32:42.873 --> 32:46.363
- I see it all!

32:46.399 --> 32:47.919
- [moans]

32:47.966 --> 32:49.706
- You stupid animal.
You stupid animal!

32:49.750 --> 32:51.400
- Court!

32:53.232 --> 32:54.932
- Mr. Deisinger!

32:54.973 --> 33:01.983
♪

33:04.460 --> 33:07.290
The black diamond,
do you have it?

33:08.638 --> 33:11.338
- I am blinded by its darkness!

33:15.210 --> 33:18.470
I see nothing, only darkness.

33:21.216 --> 33:22.906
- Then you need to see
the light.

33:24.437 --> 33:26.697
I think I can help you!

33:28.745 --> 33:30.435
- No one can help me.

33:34.969 --> 33:36.879
- Can you see the light?

33:37.928 --> 33:40.498
- I can feel it.

33:40.540 --> 33:42.150
- Grab it!

33:42.194 --> 33:49.244
♪

33:58.601 --> 34:01.561
[whirring]

34:01.604 --> 34:06.834
♪

34:06.870 --> 34:09.920
- [breathing heavily]

34:12.485 --> 34:14.525
- Where did the paintings go?

34:14.574 --> 34:17.624
- [breathing heavily]

34:19.492 --> 34:21.192
I don't know.

34:25.019 --> 34:26.539
- What just happened?

34:26.586 --> 34:33.636
♪

34:42.428 --> 34:45.038
[Staff whooshing]

34:45.083 --> 34:51.523
♪

34:51.567 --> 34:53.267
- [groans]

34:53.308 --> 34:55.218
- Mr. Deisinger?

34:56.920 --> 34:59.010
- My muse.

35:02.709 --> 35:05.229
I lost my muse.

35:08.454 --> 35:11.504
[thunder booming]

35:18.203 --> 35:19.943
- How's Mr. Deisinger?

35:19.987 --> 35:22.897
- Under psychiatric evaluation.

35:22.946 --> 35:24.686
I told him you forgot
something at school

35:24.731 --> 35:26.561
and that you found him.

35:28.256 --> 35:30.606
- He made us see things.

35:31.477 --> 35:34.347
- Things that...

35:34.393 --> 35:36.313
weren't really there.

35:39.267 --> 35:42.707
- It was like Eclipso was
working through Mr. Deisinger.

35:44.925 --> 35:46.615
It was so scary.

35:47.710 --> 35:50.150
- But he didn't have
the black diamond on him?

35:51.192 --> 35:52.632
- No.

35:55.327 --> 35:58.107
- Eclipso's getting stronger.

35:58.156 --> 36:00.506
- What do you mean?

36:02.072 --> 36:04.812
- I mean that his powers,

36:04.858 --> 36:07.558
they're spreading beyond
the black diamond.

36:07.600 --> 36:10.730
♪

36:14.172 --> 36:16.002
[birds chirping]

36:18.437 --> 36:20.087
- There you are.
[both chuckle]

36:20.134 --> 36:22.354
- We saw breakfast but not you.

36:24.182 --> 36:26.362
- Uh, Beth?

36:29.230 --> 36:31.010
- I can't pretend anymore.

36:39.022 --> 36:40.942
I found divorce papers.

36:42.112 --> 36:44.252
What is going on?

36:44.289 --> 36:45.769
I deserve to know!

36:47.596 --> 36:49.946
- Mm.
[clears throat]

36:49.990 --> 36:52.990
- It's a mutual decision.

36:53.036 --> 36:55.206
- Yeah, we just, uh...

36:56.692 --> 36:59.572
We haven't decided
to go through with it yet.

37:01.088 --> 37:03.958
Look, Beth...

37:04.004 --> 37:07.274
you know that doesn't change
how much we love you, right?

37:10.097 --> 37:12.527
- I don't understand.

37:12.578 --> 37:15.538
[soft dramatic music]

37:15.581 --> 37:18.191
♪

37:18.236 --> 37:22.146
- I really do need
to get to the hospital,

37:22.196 --> 37:26.366
but maybe we should talk more
tonight as a family.

37:26.418 --> 37:28.288
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- Yeah?

37:28.333 --> 37:31.293
- Let's--let's do that.
All right?

37:34.208 --> 37:35.778
[sighs]
Hey.

37:35.818 --> 37:42.868
♪

38:08.329 --> 38:10.639
- Why is the plan changing,
Burman?

38:10.679 --> 38:13.159
I thought it was gonna be
four on four.

38:13.203 --> 38:16.993
- Forget Cameron.
He wasn't worth the trouble.

38:17.033 --> 38:19.303
[ominous music]

38:19.340 --> 38:23.210
The diamond
is all the help we need.

38:24.214 --> 38:25.914
- What is it?

38:26.826 --> 38:29.916
- It's power that I control.

38:30.786 --> 38:33.346
- So let's get on with it.

38:33.398 --> 38:35.228
- Oh, we are.

38:35.269 --> 38:39.879
There's just one more
little piece to the puzzle.

38:39.926 --> 38:46.756
♪

38:46.802 --> 38:48.892
[laughs]

38:53.940 --> 38:56.990
[indistinct shouting]

39:00.773 --> 39:03.823
[eerie whooshing]

39:10.435 --> 39:12.305
- [gasps]

39:15.570 --> 39:17.310
[grunts]

39:17.355 --> 39:22.395
♪

39:22.447 --> 39:24.577
[ice crackling]

39:24.623 --> 39:27.103
[thunder booming]

39:27.147 --> 39:31.667
♪

39:53.652 --> 39:55.222
- Greg, move your head!
